Job Order: J0214-0754 - Permanent Full TimeTitle: Senior TesterCategory: Information TechnologyCity: Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh, IndiaJob Description: Senior Tester4-6yrsJob Location : HyderabadRequired Experience and Responsibilities / Skill-SetsExperience in Functional Testing, Manual Testing, Test Case / Script DevelopmentResponsible for writing test cases, executing them and maintaining the relevant logs.Capable of creating the test environment needed for the tests.Analyzes test results to ensure functionality is implemented correctly and recommends corrective action in case it is not so.Works with development engineers in resolution of problems.Works as a fully contributing team member under limited supervision and requires lesser technical guidance.Capable of guiding junior members in the team to help them scale up faster.Providing input to the design team to ensure that testing considerations are incorporated in the design;Development of detailed, clear, concise, and repeatable test cases;Identification, manipulation, and/or creation of test data;Reporting of test execution progress using project tools;Logging software defects;Retesting defect fixes;Submission of weekly status reports;Overseeing and monitoring of test plans for all levels of testing;Ensuring that product release bugs and changes are documented, tracked, managed, and resolved;Interacting with project team members to review functional design specifications and seeking clarification as required to complete test specifications; and,Interacting with the project team members to explain faults and review test results. At CGI, we're a team of builders. We call our employees members because all who join CGI are building their own company - one that has grown to 68,000 professionals located in 40 countries. Founded in 1976, CGI is a leading IT and business process services firm committed to helping clients succeed. We have the global resources, expertise, stability and dedicated professionals needed to achieve results for our clients - and for our members. Come grow with us. Learn more at www.cgi.com.This is a great opportunity to join a winning team. CGI offers a competitive compensation package with opportunities for growth and professional development. Benefits for full-time, permanent members start on the first day of employment and include a paid time-off program and profit participation and stock purchase plans.We wish to thank all applicants for their interest and effort in applying for this position, however, only candidates selected for interviews will be contacted.No unsolicited agency referrals please.WE ARE AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER.Skills- Functional Testing- Test Case / Script Development- Manual Testing- Automated TestingReference: 320031
